This paper deals with reinforcement learning for control with general function approximators, which is a topic that falls under the intersection of several sub-fields in computer science. The most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), as the paper deals with improving policy iteration algorithms using function approximators such as deep neural networks. The paper also touches on topics related to artificial intelligence (cs.AI), robotics (cs.RO), and control systems (cs.SY). Additionally, the paper involves optimization techniques and the use of sample-based frameworks, which are relevant to the sub-field of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS).
